This is in the parent commit:
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/39574/32/redfish-core/lib/assembly.hpp#239

@Sunnny Can you address this comment.

From const correctness point of view function with check in name should only get and check something. In bmcweb it is common to use getSomething([] {
  setSomething();
});

But it is correct, get only gets something, callback passed to get changes something. Here you are breaking this rule.

It would be better to make it a get method and pass callback which will set something for doPatch or performs additional get for doGet.

This needlessly increases indentation level. How about if (interface != "...") {
  continue;
}

This needlessly increases indentation level. How about?
if (isAssemblyAssocation) {
  return;
}

It should be done by calling a callback. In doGet you will pass:
getAssemblyProperties(aResp, chassisPath, updatedAssemblyList);

in doPatch:
setAssemblylocationIndicators(aResp, chassisPath, updatedAssemblyList, req);
